early as much as it had estimated, which was arguably a problem because it =
had sold carbon credits based on those estimates. At a meeting, a staffer a=
sked if the credits were =E2=80=9Cbased on reality,=E2=80=9D and <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35283151.285346/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
