papers properly and accurately documented the work performed on the audits.=
=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead, they just cut and pasted old audit wo=
rkpapers into new ones:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Borgers instructed BF Borgers audi=
t staff and contractors to copy workpapers from previous engagements as the=
 final workpapers for new engagements. Specifically, audit staff updated th=
e balance sheet date and date of completion on the workpapers, but all of t=
he other information indicating the substantive work done on the engagement=
